The paper discusses the preprocessing and evaluation protocols for a dataset used in recommender systems, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The proposed method for selecting a preprocessing protocol and sharing results more transparently involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) techniques. Additionally, the dataset analysis involves database (cs.DB) concepts such as data cleaning and normalization.
